<article class="module">
  <h1>How to use LearningHub</h1>

  <h3>What this is</h3>
  <p class="lead">A free, self-contained study site for the BPS Pharmacotherapy Specialty (BCPS) exam. All notes and questions are original study material written for this site — it does not reproduce ACCP or BPS copyrighted exam content. Always verify doses and recommendations against current guidelines and product labeling.</p>

  <h3>Suggested study loop</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Read</b> one module's notes in a sitting (20–40 minutes each).</li>
    <li><b>Quiz</b> yourself immediately — every question gives instant feedback with an explanation.</li>
    <li><b>Retake</b> until you score 100%; the home page tracks your best score per module.</li>
    <li><b>Rotate</b> back to weak modules on a 3–5 day cycle rather than rereading strong ones.</li>
    <li>Give <b>Biostatistics</b> extra passes — literature evaluation and statistics are among the highest-yield, most-missed areas on the exam.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Studying with a partner</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Progress is saved in each person's own browser (localStorage) — no accounts, and you'll never overwrite each other's scores.</li>
    <li>Share the site URL; each of you tracks your own module completion on the home page.</li>
    <li>Clearing browser data resets progress, so screenshot the home page if you want a record.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Exam orientation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>The BCPS exam is 175 multiple-choice questions across two sessions, heavily weighted toward direct patient care (~50%+) with substantial literature evaluation/biostatistics content.</li>
    <li>Many questions are patient cases: expect to interpret labs, choose or adjust therapy, and identify monitoring parameters — the module quizzes here mirror that style.</li>
    <li>Check <a href="https://www.bpsweb.org" rel="noopener">bpsweb.org</a> for the current content outline, eligibility, and exam windows.</li>
  </ul>
</article>
